    {
      "para_id": "p21",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Privacy by Design as the Foundation of Digital Fairness"
      ],
      "ordinal": 21,
      "text": "users while ensuring full legal compliance and maintaining high privacy standards. By combining empirical insights with our operational experience, we aim to help define practical, fair, and privacy-preserving standards for digital design.",
      "char_len": 239,
      "chunk_word_count": 32,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9711538461538461,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8702928870292888
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7339209401709401,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p22",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "Protection of Minors and Age-Appropriate Design"
      ],
      "ordinal": 22,
      "text": "Usercentrics particularly welcomes the Commission's recognition that the protection of minors must be a transversal priority of the Digital Fairness Act.",
      "char_len": 153,
      "chunk_word_count": 21,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9849624060150376,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.869281045751634
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5762218045112781,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p23",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "Protection of Minors and Age-Appropriate Design"
      ],
      "ordinal": 23,
      "text": "Children and teenagers are early adopters of digital products but also among the most vulnerable to manipulative and addictive design. In practice, effective safeguards must reflect how digital services are actually used: many can be accessed without a login, and devices such as tablets or smart TVs, are often shared within families. In such cases, neither account-based nor device-level age verification can reliably identify the actual user.",
      "char_len": 445,
      "chunk_word_count": 67,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9736147757255936,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.851685393258427
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9802110817941952,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p24",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "Protection of Minors and Age-Appropriate Design"
      ],
      "ordinal": 24,
      "text": "We therefore support measures that promote age-appropriate transparency, contextual consent flows, and parental oversight mechanisms. To be effective, these measures should remain low-friction and seamlessly integrated into the user experience, ensuring strong protection without unnecessary barriers or complexity that might otherwise encourage users to circumvent safeguards or shift toward less compliant services.",
      "char_len": 417,
      "chunk_word_count": 52,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9781420765027322,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8776978417266187
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9836065573770492,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p25",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "Protection of Minors and Age-Appropriate Design"
      ],
      "ordinal": 25,
      "text": "Usercentrics supports the development of privacy-preserving approaches to age verification and age-appropriate design that protect minors without increasing data exposure or creating new identifiers. We encourage the Commission to promote innovation in this area, including solutions that build on existing European trust frameworks such as the EU Digital Identity and Digital Wallets, to ensure that protection of minors can be achieved in a way that is both effective and privacy-respecting.",
      "char_len": 493,
      "chunk_word_count": 70,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9834905660377359,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8600405679513184
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.987617924528302,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p26",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "Fairness Through Transparency and Interoperability"
      ],
      "ordinal": 26,
      "text": "True fairness requires that consumers understand and can act on their choices across services, devices, and borders.",
      "char_len": 116,
      "chunk_word_count": 17,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.97,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8620689655172413
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5038888888888888,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p27",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "Fairness Through Transparency and Interoperability"
      ],
      "ordinal": 27,
      "text": "To achieve this, Europe needs interoperable trust infrastructure, not identical interfaces.",
      "char_len": 91,
